<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="443" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1297,2006]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1477,1502]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body mostly dark brown; frons with a cross-shaped spot. Tergites III‒IV posteriorly with two lateral patches of small pores. Tergites IV‒V with two small anterolateral patches of pores, in the middle of each group of pores, two ovoid scars. Tergite III‒V with a pair of large ovoid scars, located on the posterior half of each tergite. Sternite IX subpentagonal in ventral view, with posterior edge rounded. Pseudopenal membrane with a subtriangular region devoid of spinules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1297,2006]" box="[199,654,1657,1682]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1657,1682]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">Description.</emphasis>
Based on one pinned male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1297,2006]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1693,1718]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">Head.</emphasis>
Labrum light brown, with a small circular spot in the middle, clypeus brown, mandibles amber, labial and maxillary palpi brown. Frons yellow-ochre, with dark brown cross-shaped mark (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1222,1729,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
Fig 
<number box="[1192,1222,1729,1754]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Scape ventrally ochre, dorsally brown, pedicel brown, flagellum with 
<number box="[771,799,1765,1790]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="26.0">26</number>
articles, dark brown, densely covered with dark brown setae. Vertex pale ochre, with two dark brown triangular spots behind of the antennal sockets (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1311,1801,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
Fig. 
<number box="[1281,1311,1801,1826]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Occiput dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1297,2006]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1873,1898]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">Thorax.</emphasis>
Prothorax length, 3.5 mm; pronotum predominantly brown (
<figureCitation box="[998,1084,1873,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
Fig. 
<number box="[1053,1084,1874,1898]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
a). Meso- and metanotum dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[238,321,1909,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
Fig. 
<number box="[290,321,1910,1934]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
e). Pteropleura predominantly ochre, with brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[945,1027,1909,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
Fig. 
<number box="[997,1027,1909,1934]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,1297,2006]" lastBlockId="43.[151,1437,151,248]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1945,1970]" pageId="42" pageNumber="443">Legs.</emphasis>
Foreleg with coxa brown, trochanter brown. Femur (length, 3.5 mm) with inner surface dark reddish brown in the middle, light reddish brown at the periphery, including sub-basal spine; outer surface brown, with minor spines reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[482,566,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[535,566,152,176]" pageId="43" pageNumber="444" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
c). All segments covered with abundant brown setae. Mid- and hindlegs with coxae brown, trochanter dark brown, femora and tibiae brown. First tarsomere very long; last tarsomere brown dorsally. Claws amber with three apical teeth. All segments densely covered with ochre or brown setae.
</paragraph>
