species. Elevation in meters.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,1841,2010]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,281,1841,1866]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing length, 
<quantity box="[493,577,1842,1866]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
; membrane hyaline, venation dark brown, except basal half of the AA and AP 
<number box="[191,200,1878,1902]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
that are pale yellow. Pterostigma dark brown. Costal field hyaline, with eight crossveins; subcostal field light amber with 
<number box="[295,364,1914,1938]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10‒11</number>
crossveins. Four veins extending posteriorly from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1055,1914,1937]" name="Poland" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">RP</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1076,1163,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1133,1163,1913,1938]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
f). Hindwing similar to forewing, length 
<quantity box="[350,435,1950,1974]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
; membrane hyaline; costal field with five crossveins; four veins extending posteriorly from the 
<collectingCountry box="[253,287,1986,2009]" name="Poland" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">RP</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[303,385,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1973,1995]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,301,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[151,1436,301,1952]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 23. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, head and thorax, dorsal; b, pteropleura; c, head, frontal; d, forelegs; e, pteronotum, dorsal; f, fore- and hindwing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236838/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[355,385,1985,2010]" pageId="46" pageNumber="447" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,151,176]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergite I ochre, tergite II and III brown; tergites IV and V with a subtriangular dark brown spot, within this a pair of central ochre spots. Tergites VI‒IX medially with longitudinal dark brown stripe, extended posterolaterally on each tergite. Sternites predominantly brown, with posterior corners dark brown; sternites IV‒IX with dark brown central stripe. Sternum IX with posterior margin rounded, dark brown, with long ochre setae. Pleural membrane dark brown from fifth segment. Male pregenital abdominal apparatus: tergites III and IV with two lateral patches of circular pores at the posterior border, with about 
<number box="[943,1013,332,357]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="22.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="18.0">18‒26</number>
on tergite III and 
<number box="[1214,1283,332,357]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="33.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="30.0">30‒36</number>
on tergite IV. Tergites IV‒V with two anterolateral patches of pores irregularly arranged in two rows, with approximately 
<number box="[1372,1400,367,392]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="54.0">54</number>
on the tergite IV and 
<number box="[359,429,404,429]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="59.0" valueMax="64.0" valueMin="54.0">54‒64</number>
on tergite V, in the middle of each group of pores, two ovoid scars. Tergite III‒V with a pair of large ovoid scars, located on the posterior half of each tergite (
<figureCitation box="[931,1014,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[983,1014,440,464]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,476,501]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Ectoproct elongated, ovoid in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[883,969,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[938,969,476,500]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
c), densely covered with long dark setae; ventromedial lobe slightly sclerotized, with about 
<number box="[718,746,512,536]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="12.0">12</number>
short setae, slightly thickened. Sternite IX sub-pentagonal in ventral view, with posterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[667,752,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[721,752,548,572]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
e), in lateral view the apex reaches the level of the gonarcus apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[267,350,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[319,350,583,608]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Gonarcal median lobe arched, as long or slightly longer than pseudopenis, with apex rounded, slender in frontal view and widened in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[747,831,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[800,831,620,645]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Mediuncus slightly widened in the anterior half in lateral view, distally forked in ventral view, with projections attenuated, slightly widened (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1259,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[1228,1259,655,680]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
b). Gonocoxites narrow, medially curved with apex rounded in ventral view. Hypandrium internum triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1412,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[1382,1412,692,717]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
f). Pseudopenal membrane with a subtriangular region lacking of spinules. Hypomeres present as two lateral granules. Pseudopenis as long as pseudopenal membrane (
<figureCitation box="[696,779,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1866,1888]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,199,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 24. Leptomantispa hoffmani: a, male pregenital abdominal apparatus; b, male genitalia, ventral; c, male terminalia, dorsal; d, male genitalia, lateral; e, sternite IX, ventral; f, hypandrium internum. Abbreviations: gonarcus (g), gonocoxite (gcx), hypomere (hpm), pore (po), pseudopenal membrane (ppm), scar (sc). Scale bars, 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236839/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[748,779,764,789]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,151,1256]" box="[199,418,799,824]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,799,824]" pageId="47" pageNumber="448">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
